biography_text: DUFFY, Sean, a Representative from Wisconsin; born in Hayward, Sawyer County, Wis., October 3, 1971; B.A., St. Mary's College, Winona, Minn., 1994; J.D., William Mitchell College of Law, St. Paul, Minn., 1999; lawyer, private practice; prosecutor, Ashland County, Wis.; acting assistant district attorney and district attorney, Ashland County, Wis., 2002-2010; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred Twelfth and to the four succeeding Congresses (January 3, 2011-present).

post_secondary_degrees.institution: William Mitchell College of Law, St. Paul, Minn.
